{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01MWrWt7yamqJsn6i6TCS4GH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is clear:\n```\nTransport SSL must be enabled if security is enabled. Please set [xpack.security.transport.ssl.enabled] to [true] or disable security by setting [xpack.security.enabled] to [false]\n```\n\nWhen security is enabled in Elasticsearch 8.x, transport SSL must also be enabled. But the TLS cert we have is an HTTP cert (tls.crt/tls.key/ca.crt). I need to also enable transport SSL.\n\nThe problem is that the existing `es-http-tls` secret has TLS certs, but we need to use those for transport SSL too, or we need separate certs for transport.\nSince security must stay enabled for HTTPS access with the elastic user, I'll reuse the same certificate for transport SSL. The main concern is whether the cert is valid for the node identities in a multi-node setup, but for now I'll try using the existing cert for both HTTP and transport.\n\nI'll configure transport SSL with certificate verification mode set to `certificate` instead of `full` to bypass hostname verification issues, then update the ConfigMap accordingly.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6415,"cache_read_input_tokens":32029,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":6415},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fd259128-069b-45cd-b525-e5e3bdceb713","uuid":"18a739e6-ee37-4d75-b36e-0965c9c5aa04","request_id":"req_011CcQ92R37pnyXBU88436uD"}
