{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01YE8ZhF1igDv3uKniTt3Hy4","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pod is stuck in CrashLoopBackOff and is not starting new containers. The `rollout restart` may not have taken effect yet because the pod is in backoff. The logs I'm seeing are from 14:29 which was the original creation time, not after the restart. The pod may still be in backoff mode.\n\nThe key issue is that the ConfigMap update might not have triggered a restart of the pod because Kubernetes StatefulSets with `rollout restart` change a `kubectl.kubernetes.io/restartedAt` annotation on the pod template. But since the pod is in CrashLoopBackOff, it might not get the new pod template until the old pod is terminated.\nI should delete the pod to force it to pick up the new configuration, though the `rollout restart` command should have already added the restartedAt annotation to trigger pod recreation. The real problem might be that the ConfigMap changes aren't taking effect because the pod is still mounting the old version, and while Kubernetes does update mounted ConfigMaps automatically, there's typically a delay involved.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2349,"cache_read_input_tokens":40970,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2349},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fd259128-069b-45cd-b525-e5e3bdceb713","uuid":"08bb822d-0f23-49ff-8c81-c6aceaeeee40","request_id":"req_011CcQ95VmxkFT1jBr9hm7up"}
