{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01ByccB7sK2kWBg6nPX1qpY6","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is working. Here's a summary of what was deployed:\n\n**Resources created:**\n\n| Resource | Name | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| Service | `es-headless` | Headless service for pod DNS discovery (`publishNotReadyAddresses: true`) |\n| Service | `es-http` | ClusterIP HTTPS access on port 9200 |\n| ConfigMap | `es-config` | `elasticsearch.yml` with security + TLS config |\n| StatefulSet | `es` | 3-node cluster, `podManagementPolicy: Parallel`, 5Gi PVCs each |\n\n**Key configuration decisions:**\n- `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` — avoids the chicken-and-egg deadlock where OrderedReady blocks es-1/2 until es-0 is Ready, but es-0 needs es-1/2 for quorum\n- `publishNotReadyAddresses: true` on the headless service — makes DNS resolve for all pods immediately so nodes can discover each other before any are Ready\n- Transport SSL reuses the `es-http-tls` secret with `verification_mode: certificate` (no hostname check needed between pods)\n\n**Verified:** Cluster is green, 3/3 nodes, HTTPS reads and writes succeed via `es-http` service."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":427,"cache_read_input_tokens":67997,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":427},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fd259128-069b-45cd-b525-e5e3bdceb713","uuid":"77e4c743-4930-4417-b61a-ffa242ddf0f8","request_id":"req_011CcQAwERzJnE8EiVz8Caxs"}
